Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp}, half the @garlic powder{1/2%tsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}, and remaining @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}; season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

> TIP: If you like things spicy, add a dash of the hot sauce—just be sure to save some for forming your patties!

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @Frank's Seasoning Blend{7.2%g}, a dash of @Frank's Hot Sauce{1}, and salt. Form into two patties (four patties for 4 servings), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}; cover pan to melt cheese.

> GRILLING ALTERNATIVE: Heat a well-oiled #grill{} or #grill pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness (we suggest 3-5 minutes per side, but grills can vary). In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with Monterey Jack; cover to melt cheese.

While patties cook, halve and toast @potato buns{2}. Spread cut sides of buns with creamy ranch sauce, then fill with patties and @crispy fried onions{1}.

Divide burgers between plates and serve with potato wedges on the side.